description: Suske en Wiske is one of the most popular comic books in Belgium and the Netherlands. The story was first written and drawn by Willy Vandersteen in 1945 and published in several newspapers. In 1946 it was collected in a comic. In 1972 Paul Geerts took over as the writer and artist. Since 1946 more than 300 stories have appeared. The stories have been translated in approximately 25 languages and dialects. These stories are mostly self contained stories although references are made in various issues to other issues to understand the full story.
